.SH NAME
.
acprun \- Execute parallel jobs using ACP library.

.\" **************************
.\"    Synopsis Section
.\" **************************
.SH SYNOPSIS
.
.PP
Execute parallel jobs using ACP library:

.B acprun
[ options ]
.B <program>
[ <args> ] :
.P

.
.\" **************************
.\"    Quick Summary Section
.\" **************************
.SH QUICK SUMMARY
.
If you are simply looking for how to run an ACP application, you probably use acprun as follows:

    \fB%\fP acprun [ -np nprocs ] [ --acp-nodefile=nodefile ]  <program> <args>

This will run nprocs copies of \fI<program>\fR in your current run-time environment.
ACP's \fIacprun\fR will use \fIssh\fR as the process starter.
Processes are started on the hosts specified in the nodefile.
If --acp-nodefile option is not specified, nprocs processes will run on the localhost without using ssh.
.
.\" **************************
.\"    Options Section
.\" **************************
.SH OPTIONS
.
.\"
.\" Start options listing
.\"    Indent 10 characters from start of first column to start of second column
.TP 10
.B <program>
The program executable. This is identified as the first non-recognized argument
to acprun.
.
.
.TP
.B <args>
Pass these run-time arguments to every new process.
.
.
.TP
.B -np nprocs\fR, \fP --acp-nprocs=nprocs
Run nprocs copies of the program on the given nodes.
Without this option, acprun automatically execute one program.
\fIPlease note\fR that "\fI-np\fR nprocs" has to be \fIfirst option\fR of acprun command.
There are no such limitations for "--acp-nprocs=nprocs" option.
.
.
.TP
.B --acp-node=nodefile
Provide a nodefile to use.
Without this option, nprocs processes will run on the localhost without using ssh.
In nodefile, hostnames have to be simply written line by line.
   \fB%\fP cat nodefile
   hostname0
   hostname1
   hostname2
   ...
.
.
.TP
.B ---envnet=networkdevice
Provide a networkdevice value. (ex. UDP, IB)
Default value is determined during the installation configure procedure.
.
.
.TP
.B --acp-startermemsize=memsize
Provide a starter memory size used in ACP library. \" (default: 1024 Byte)
.
.
.TP
.B --acp-help
Display help for this command
.
.
.TP
.B  --acp-version
Display version number.
.
.TP
.B Other --acp-* otions
Parsed as error in regard to invalid option even though that option is used as user program option.
.
.
